                  <persName>
                  <t:roleName xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="title">ʾabuna</t:roleName>
               </persName>
                  <nationality type="Ethiopia"/>
                  <faith type="EOTC"/>
               <occupation type="ecclesiastic">16th century abbot of May Barāzyo (Tigray)</occupation>
                
               <floruit> He was a monk who is said in his Miracles to have been the son of 
                  <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10303Yekunno">Yǝkunno ʾAmlāk</persName> and a spiritual disciple of  a certain 
                  
                  
                    ʾabbā  Yoḥannǝs Kamā. 
                  He left the secular life during the reign 
                  of King <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10111WedemR">Wǝdǝm Raʿad</persName>. </floruit>
                  <death/>
               </person>  
               
               
